Intro3
------------------------------------------------------------------------
"Opening the pod," Luke says indifferently. The thick brown door slides aside. Behind it is a claustrophobically small, round chamber with two seats and a console.


"Enter the location's coordinates," you command, placing yourself in one of the seats and fastening the belt.


"Done."


"Launch!"


The door snaps shut, suppressing the wailing fire alarm. The soft foam rubber interior of the cabin gives you a short illusion of comfort which is destroyed within a moment as the acceleration of the launch blast jams you into the seat like a giant hammer. The spherical pod parts from the ship and swirls through the vacuum like a huge tennis ball until the nozzles stabilize its trajectory. Lightness overcomes you. You draw breath and blink away the sweat from your eye lids. It floats in front of your face, weightless.


...